Re: Bitcoin minting is thermodynamically perverse

Bitcointalk

2010-08-09 21:28:39 UTC - [11]Original Post

   The heat from your computer is not wasted if you need to heat your
   home.  If youʼre using electric heat where you live, then your
   computerʼs heat isnʼt a waste.  Itʼs equal cost if you generate the
   heat with your computer.
   If you have other cheaper heating than electric, then the waste is only
   the difference in cost.
   If itʼs summer and youʼre using A/C, then itʼs twice.
   Bitcoin generation should end up where itʼs cheapest.  Maybe that will
   be in cold climates where thereʼs electric heat, where it would be
   essentially free.
